-- Vestas Opens China Technology Research, Development Center
-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   W i e n b e r g
-- 2010-10-12T08:31:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/vestas-wind-opens-china-technology-research-development-center-in-beijing.html
Vestas Wind Systems A/S, the world’s
largest maker of wind turbines, said it today opened a
technology research and development center in Beijing, China.  Vestas will invest $50 million over five years in the site
and double the center’s staff to more than 200 engineers and
technology specialists in 2012, the Randers, Denmark-based
company said on its website today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christian Wienberg at 
 cwienberg@bloomberg.net  